<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3696> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3696" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Brought unsuccessful prosecutions against P. Furius (Tr. Pl. 99), which he lost because he expressed regret for the death of Saturninus (Cic. Rab. Perd. 24-25; Val. Max. 8.1, damn. 2; cf. Schol. Bob. 95 Stangl), and against Valerius Flaccus (Aed. Cur. 99; Cic. Flacc. 77), and when he was himself prosecuted and condemned after his year of office he departed to live in Asia (Cic. Flacc. 77, and Schol. Bob. 95 Stangl; Val. Max. 8.1, damn. 2)." .
